    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Survival after invasive coronary revascularization is worse in patients with chronic kidney
      disease than in those without it. The investigators aimed to examine whether oral
      administration of nicorandil, a hybrid of nitrate and adenosine triphosphate-sensitive
      potassium channel opener, could improve the survival of end-stage renal disease patients with
      coronary artery disease by inhibiting cardiac death after coronary revascularization.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
